# Global ignore list for GNU Stow.
#
# This prevents Stow from trying to link common OS/tooling junk files that can
# accidentally end up inside stow packages (and can cause conflicts at $HOME).
#
# Stow treats entries here as regular expressions (one per line).
#
# What the "aggressive" bits might ignore (intentionally):
# - zsh history/session files (you said you don't need to sync these)
# - zsh completion dumps (.zcompdump*)
# - vim/neovim swap/backup/session artifacts
#
# This should not ignore "real config" you likely want to stow, such as:
# - .zshrc / .config/zsh/*
# - init.lua, lua/ configs, plugin lockfiles, etc.

# macOS Finder metadata
(^|/)\.DS_Store$

# macOS volume/system metadata
(^|/)\.AppleDouble$
(^|/)\.LSOverride$
(^|/)\.Spotlight-V100$
(^|/)\.Trashes$
(^|/)\.Trash$
(^|/)\.fseventsd$
(^|/)\.TemporaryItems$

# Windows metadata
(^|/)Thumbs\.db$
(^|/)Desktop\.ini$

# zsh runtime artifacts (do not stow)
(^|/)\.zcompdump($|\..*)
(^|/)\.zsh_history$
(^|/)\.zsh_sessions(/|$)
(^|/).*\.zwc$

# vim/neovim runtime artifacts (do not stow)
(^|/).*\.sw[pon]$
(^|/).*\.swn$
(^|/).*\.(un~)$
(^|/)(Session\.vim|Sessionx\.vim)$

# Common editor/backup files
(^|/).*\~$
(^|/)\.bak$
(^|/)\.tmp$

# Archive artifacts (occasionally created by GUI tools)
(^|/).__MACOSX$
